<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN288-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai - tumpai; tuṟai - mūtiṉmullai. kaḻāttalaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>  
    <div xml:id="PN288">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>maṇkoḷa varinta vainnuti maruppi</l>
<l>ṉaṇṇa ṉallē ṟiraṇṭuṭaṉ maṭuttu</l>
<l>veṉṟataṉ paccai cīvātu pōrtta</l>
<l>tiṇpiṇi muraca miṭaippulat tiraṅka</l>
<l>vāramar mayaṅkiya ñāṭpiṟ ṟeṟuvara</l>
<l>neṭuvēl pāynta nāṇuṭai neñcat</l>
<l>tarukukai<gap quantity="44" reason="lost" unit="character"/>maṉṟa</l>
<l>kurutiyoṭu tuyalvaru mārpiṉ</l>
<l>muyakkiṭai yīyātu moyttaṉa paruntē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While in the fields the drum with firm straps sounds,</l>
<l>covered, without cleaning [it], with the fresh hide of the one that was victorious,</l>
<l>after two majestic good bulls had gored each other,</l>
<l>[their] horns with sharp tips, lined with earth so that it sticks,</l>
<l>while a difficult battle rages with confused fighting,</l>
<l>with a heart that possesses the shame [of weakness] when long spears leapt,</l>
<l>???</l>
<l>kites swarmed without giving space for embracing</l>
<l>the chest heaving with blood.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
